The rise was attributed to the increased number of corporate failures as
well as greater public awareness of the DTI's investigations unit.
The number of convictions stemming from those investigations rose to eight
in the first quarter of this year, compared with three in the previous
quarter.
Some of the convictions stem from investigations which were opened as long
